# VibeKB (Cursor rule)

This repository uses **VibeKB** to explain what the software currently does. The
knowledge base and tooling live under `.vibekb/`. This file is a namespaced
pointer that VibeKB owns; it does not touch your other Cursor rules.

## Every session

- **Orient:** `vibekb status` (or `php .vibekb/runtime/tools/vibekb.php status`) —
  provenance, current work, the handoff's next action, and drift.
- **The canonical operating rules** live in
  [`.vibekb/reference/WORKFLOW.md`](../../.vibekb/reference/WORKFLOW.md). Read it
  before meaningful work; if anything here disagrees, that file wins.

## The lifecycle

orient → record work (`.vibekb/work/current.md`) → implement → find impact
(`vibekb affected --since <base>`) → verify honestly → update the living model
(records, memory, diagrams, provenance) → update the handoff → `vibekb check`.

## Honesty

Distinguish intended / implemented / verified behaviour. Never claim a
`verified-*` state you did not confirm, and never imply VibeKB auto-updates —
it is agent-maintained. See [`.vibekb/reference/PRODUCT.md`](../../.vibekb/reference/PRODUCT.md).
